   ``King of the Hill,'' Fox at 8: Unathletic Bobby joins the
football team, and Hank is an assistant coach. With the season
about to begin, this might be a family discussion starter. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CABLE CAST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``And the nominees are ...'' MTV at 8: Special previewing of
next Thursday's 2000 MTV Video Music Awards.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sex and the City,'' HBO at 9: ``Don't Ask, Don't Tell'' is the
episode title. Carrie contemplates telling Aidan about her affair
with Big. Meanwhile, the night before their wedding, Charlotte
realizes that Trey may not be the perfect man. But Samantha's
already celebrating with one of the groomsmen.
</P>
<P>
   ``Daria,'' MTV at 9: Back-to-back episodes of this underrated
animated comedy. A kitchen fire and a bad hair dye mistake are the
topics. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Sopranos,'' HBO at 10: The fish talk to Tony, and Big
Pussy goes over the side. Rerun.
</P>
<P>
   ``South Park,'' Comedy Central at 10: Another chosen-by-viewers
rerun favorite.
</P>
<P>
   ``Soul Food,'' Showtime at 10: Maxine discovers a secret between
her husband and sister.
</P>
