<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Prepare to go back in time with the next hot game
 &HT;    By D.A. Serra
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Capcom, known for its 'Street Fighter' and
'Resident Evil' series for Nintendo and PlayStation, is set to blow
the roof off of computer animation with its new Onimusha: Warlords
adventure game for PlayStation2. Its technical achievements in
animation were recently awarded Best of Show at the SIGGRAPH 2000
computer graphics conference for the game's opening movie and
optical motion system, which capture six samurais battling
simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
   Warlords is being touted as one of the most technically advanced
video games conceived for the PlayStation2. The game is an epic
saga of 16th-century Japan, when warlords launched attacks against
one another and fought battles in the name of power. Players are
samurai warriors who must fight their way into a castle to save a
princess. A 200-piece orchestra performs the original musical
score. The technology creates finely detailed character graphics
that show life-like emotions.
</P>
<P>
   The release date is set for this winter.
</P>
