<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Fridge magnets of the future
 &HT;    By Shaun Conlin
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ If the hybrid word ``RubberSteel'' sounds like
something out of Star Trek, then the future is now. The MagZone has
a variety of ShowOffs Photo Print Sheets ($4 to $6 depending on
package; www .magzone.com) for all your ``Craft-eze'' needs.
Malleable rubber stock laced with magnetized steel and peel-away
adhesive allows for the sticking and posting of just about anything
you wish to affix to your fridge, file cabinet or fire door _ the
most obviously implied of which would be photographs or artwork.
RubberSteel is also easily cut to fit with scissors or a blade.
Similarly available are standard-size Magnetic Photo Frames (two
for $3.60), which are without adhesive but come with a pre-cut hole
to both enshrine and hold a picture against any flat metal surface.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
