&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A case of virtual indestructibility
 &HT;    By Shaun Conlin
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Because translucent colors are all the rage _ as
if working at the computer is supposed to be pretty _ Case Logic
offers translucent, fruity-colored CD-ROM cases ($6;
www.caselogic.com). A fairly durable plastic casing houses typical
soft cloth pouches with clear plastic faces for your ROM organizing
needs. Through elaborate testing methods, I found that the unit and
the snap on its hinging lock remain intact and functional even
after the case is ``accidentally'' dropped on the floor repeatedly.
However, they tend to crack when hurled full-force against a cement
wall. Still, pretty impressive. And since all four fruity colors
are so pleasant to behold, odds are they'll subdue any full-force,
item-chucking, temper-tantrum impulses.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
