</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Research homework on the Web
 &HT;    By Robert W. Gee
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.studyweb.com _ Homework may not be too tough after just one
week of school, but here's one to bookmark for later. This site is
a great portal for finding information on the Web about topics from
algebra to Zoroastrianism. It links you to a wealth of sites,
organized under 30 subject areas and hundreds more subheadings.
Biology, for example, is broken into 45 sub-areas, including
cloning and genetics. Also, be sure to check out the homework help
page at www.studyweb.com/HomeworkHelp/toc.htm.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
