</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    This day in history
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   Every day is another big day in history. If you want to discover
the important events that happened on this very date, click on
memory.loc.gov/ammem/today/. The Library of Congress' America
Memory collection contains facts sure to entertain and educate. So
log on, learn more and maybe one day your birthday will be added to
the LOC's list.
</P>
<P>
   HE'S BAAAAAACK!
</P>
<P>
   R.L. Stine, that is. The ``Goosebumps'' author is haunting book
shelves again, with a new series called ``The Nightmare Room.'' The
first two books, ``Don't Forget Me!'' and ``Locker 13''
(Avon/Parachute, $3.99 each), are in stores now. Don't expect ``The
Nightmare Room'' to have as many wild twists as ``Goosebumps.''
Stine's new focus: everyday kids who find themselves in situations
``one step beyond reality.'' For more: www.thenightmareroom.com.
</P>
<P>
   EYES ON GOOD VISION
</P>
<P>
   Did you know that one in four school-aged children has a vision
problem? Whether you have perfect eyesight or need specs to see the
blackboard, the Eye Rock Club can teach you fun and easy ways to
take care of your eyes. Kids 18 years and younger can sign up for
the club at local WalMart Vision Centers. You'll receive eyecare
newsletters with membership. Register before Sept. 9, and you can
enter to win a $500 WalMart shopping spree.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
