<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ George W. Bush's response to Al
Gore's scrappy acceptance speech vowing to fight for ``working
families'' was to accuse Gore of practicing ``class warfare.'' So?
All politics are about the struggle for primacy among competing
social and economic interests. Both Gore and Bush have tailored
appeals to specific income levels. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
