   ENTREPRENEURS VS. EXECUTIVES AT SOCABA.COM
</P>
<P>
   HOT-STARTUP-CASE-STUDY-HARVARD-BUSINESS-REVIEW _ At some point
in the upward trajectory of every hot start-up, professional
managers are called in to help unseasoned young entrepreneurs run
the place. But sometimes the insiders and outsiders don't see
things eye to eye. Will that dynamic sink Socaba.com? Two
commentators offer advice in response to this fictional case study.
PLEASE NOTE: Because of the length of this article, editors may
elect to delete one of the reactions from commentators. 1,700
words. By Regina Fazio Maruca.
</P>
