<HEADLINE>
A CONVERSATION WITH SEAMAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (Eds: For use with GAME-SEAMAN-REVIEW-SFCHRON)  
 c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;   &LR; PLAYER: Where are you from, Seaman?
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: I'm from all over the place.
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: Yeah? Like where?
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: (Narrowing his eyes) Why?
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: I'm just curious.
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: I think you need to get out more often.
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: Well, I also want to know because ... because ...
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: (Cocking an eyebrow) Yes?
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: Because I think I'm in love with you.
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: (Scowling) Oh, har-de-har-har-har. I'm a fish, remember?
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: I know. But you're cute.
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: Don't think I don't know it.
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: Can I just have a kiss?
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: (Slyly) It'll cost you a dollar.
</P>
<P>
   PLAYER: You're cheap.
</P>
<P>
   SEAMAN: You need to get a life.
</P>
