<P>
   So, there's your list of why I expect the markets to rally here.
I am sure that there will be potholes along the way _ potholes that
will be well covered, no, make that overcovered, by the media. When
we stumble into them, refer to this list. It is more powerful than
any of those ruts in the road.
</P>
<P>
   (James J. Cramer is manager of a hedge fund and co-founder of
TheStreet.com. At time of publication, his fund was long Ariba,
AT&AMP;T, AT&AMP;T Wireless, Brocade, Exodus, IBM, Intel, Cisco and Nortel.
His fund often buys and sells securities that are the subject of
his columns, both before and after the columns are published, and
the positions that his fund takes may change at any time. Under no
circumstances does the information in this column represent a
recommendation to buy or sell stocks. Cramer's writings provide
insights into the dynamics of money management and are not a
solicitation for transactions. While he cannot provide investment
advice or recommendations, he invites you to send comments on his
column at jjcletters(at)thestreet.com.
</P>
