<HEADLINE>
HOT TRAVEL DEALS 
</HEADLINE>
  (For release Sunday, Sept. 3) 
 By JOSEPH SIANO    
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEDITERRANEAN AUTUMN _ First European Cruises has seven
discounted sailings out of Genoa aboard its 800-passenger Flamenco
this autumn. The 11-night trips sail the western Mediterranean, and
among the ports of call are Almeria (for a trip to Granada),
Malaga, Funchal, Tenerife and Lanzarote in Spain; Safi (for
Marrakesh) and Casablanca in Morocco, and Marseille. Departures are
Oct. 12 and 23; Nov. 3, 14 and 25 and Dec. 16 and 26. Rates range
from $890 to $2,590 a person, based on double occupancy, for the
October and November sailings (versus $1,710 to $3,690 originally);
December cruises are $1,520 to $2,650 a person, double ($2,000 to
$3,690 originally). Round-trip air fare to Genoa is extra. A
package of eight shore excursions costs $491 a person. The Flamenco
has a fitness center, movie theater and casino. Cabins have phones
and TV. Call First European, (888) 983-8767.
</P>
<P>
   SLIMMER RATES _ From Oct. 1 to Dec. 21, the Safety Harbor Resort
and Spa, on Tampa Bay, is dropping prices on its introductory spa
package 20 percent. Three nights' accommodations, three meals a day
for three days and a daily 25-minute massage are $372 a person,
double occupancy, and $497 single. Guests have access to all spa
facilities, including daily exercise classes, and, in case the walk
from the parking lot is too exhausting, free valet parking. A 17.5
percent service charge and taxes are extra. Call (888) 237-8772.
</P>
<P>
   WALES BY RAIL _ Sometimes, savings come by slicing off unwanted
options. For those who want to visit Wales by rail but don't want
to pay for a BritRail Pass, the Freedom of Wales Flexi Pass comes
in two lengths. The shorter one allows four days of unlimited rail
travel over eight days and bus travel all eight days, for $85 (a
four-day pass for all of Britain is $235). A pass with eight days
of rail travel over 15 days (again, with bus travel all 15 days
included) is $159. Connections to Wales from selected cities in
England are included, as are discount admissions to castles and
other attractions. Rail travel does not have to be undertaken on
consecutive days, but must begin after 9 a.m. on weekdays. Passes
must be purchased before leaving the United States. Call (877)
677-1006.
</P>
<P>
   FARES TO ISRAEL _ Funjet Vacations has round-trip flights to Tel
Aviv that start at $634 from Kennedy Airport for travel Nov. 1 to
Dec. 12 and Dec. 25 to March 31. From Tuesday through Oct. 31 and
Dec. 13 to 24, it's $779. Fares are identical from Boston. From
Chicago, they are $714 or $904, based on the same low-high periods,
and from Los Angeles or San Francisco, $789 and $929. The carriers
are Swissair or Sabena and fares are based on midweek travel and
can be booked up to a week before departure. International fees and
taxes are extra. Call Funjet at (800) 558-3000; reservation
operators should be asked for the K-class fares.
</P>
