 &QL; 
 &UR; Joe Eszterhas &LR; , the semi-porno screenwriter whose latest literary
work provided  &UR; President Clinton &LR; 's organ with the power of speech,
strikes out against  &UR; Al Gore &LR;  and  &UR; Joe Lieberman  &LR; in a full-page ad
in Aug. 29's Variety.
</P>
<P>
   In a lengthy open letter to members of the entertainment
industry, Eszterhas warns of the dangers of the Democratic
candidates' sermonizing about the moral perils of popular culture.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm a writer who likes pushing the envelope, and Joe Lieberman
frightens me,'' Eszterhas says. ``No more Hollywood money for Al
Gore. . . . Let's make Joe Lieberman accountable for his rhetoric.
Not a penny more until he `clarifies' his position to the
satisfaction of our creative freedom.''
</P>
