   _  &UR; Elmore Leonard  &LR; writes all his books in longhand on unlined
pads, he told GQ. ``My handwriting goes up, which I'm happy to hear
is a good thing.  &UR; Hemingway &LR; 's went down something awful, like a
waterfall. He was my first big influence because he made writing
look easy. Then I realized that Hemingway didn't have much of a
sense of humor. So I had to find someone else.'' He doesn't say who
the someone else was.
