latest issue, on the importance of writing letters, especially to
say thank you. ``A good way to start a letter is to ask a question.
Takes a little practice to learn to do that, but try openings like
. . . `Did you rent my dinner companion from the U.N.? He knew
 &LR; everything &LR;  about Sierra Leone.' ''
</P>
<P>
