<P>
   (NYT13) PORTLAND, Ore. -- Aug. 28, 2000 --
SCI-MEN-OSTEOPOROSIS-1 -- Osteoporosis, known as the ``silent
disease,'' often has no symptoms until the bones are so
comporomised that a minor trauma causes a fracture. As awareness of
osteoporosis in postmenopausal women has grown, it has become more
common for them to get routine bone density tests. Men, though, are
rarely given bone density tests unless they have significant
symptoms. Dr. Eric Orwoll, of the Mark Hatfield Research Center,
says the strong link between osteoporosis and women often leads to
overlooking the problem in men. (Shane Young/The New York Times)
